<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Steeltoe 411</h2>
        <p>Steeltoe is an extension of Pivotal Cloud Foundry (PCF) that allows .Net developers to benefit from Pivotal's PaaS product. Using Steeltoe developers can capture full PCF platform advantages such as failing fast with <a href="https://github.com/Netflix/Hystrix/wiki" target="_blank">Hystrix</a>, mid-tier load balancing and failover with <a href="https://github.com/Netflix/eureka/wiki/Eureka-at-a-glance" target="_blank">Eureka</a> plus configuration and Pivotal Marketplace services for your applications.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>About PCF</h2>
        <p>Application development is severely hampered by an extended deployment process and the benefit of using PCF is the ability to create and run applications quickly, and then run them with assurance that they will be resilient and continue to run without intervention. Time to market is money earned for most companies, thus expenditures for deployment services are offset by decreasing that time.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <h2>Platform Choices</h2>
        <p>Rather than forcing your application into one vendor's version of cloud services, PCF allows you to choose where the components of your application will run based on what is best for your application. For companies already heavily vested in the Microsoft stack Azure is the outstanding choice.
        </p>
    </div>
